08/04/2008
ZAGREB, Croatia -- A court in Vukovar launched a trial Monday (April 7th) against Croatian Serb Bogdan Kuzmic, who is charged with war crimes committed during the 1991 fall of the town. 
Kuzmic, 47, is charged with crimes against civilians who had sought refuge in the hospital in Vukovar, where he was working when the town was besieged by the Yugoslav People's Army. 
According to the indictment, on November 18th 1991, Kuzmic chose five civilians and took them away. 
They have never been found. 
(HINA, AFP - 07/04/08)
